{\"ngram\": \"the Florida black bear\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4063}, {\"ngram\": \"the vocal opposition\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 4094, \"to\": 4101}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The state-sanctioned hunt began Saturday, after drawing more than 160,000 applications for a far more limited number of hunting permits, including from opponents who are trying to reduce the number of bears killed in this year's hunt, the state's first since 2015, The Associated Press reported.\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4373, \"end\": 4389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999995452526, \"rank\": 4.5474480644892836e-10, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The state-sanctioned hunt\", \"from\": 4104, \"to\": 4129}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 160,000 applications\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4190}, {\"ngram\": \"a far more limited number\", \"from\": 4195, \"to\": 4220}, {\"ngram\": \"hunting permits\", \"from\": 4224, \"to\": 4239}, {\"ngram\": \"opponents\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4265}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 4291, \"to\": 4301}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 4305, \"to\": 4310}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's hunt\", \"from\": 4321, \"to\": 4337}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission awarded 172 bear hunt permits by random lottery for this year's season, allowing hunters to kill one bear each in areas where the population is deemed large enough.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4405, \"end\": 4412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"172 bear hunt permits\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4484}, {\"ngram\": \"random lottery\", \"from\": 4488, \"to\": 4502}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's season\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4525}, {\"ngram\": \"hunters\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4543}, {\"ngram\": \"one bear\", \"from\": 4552, \"to\": 4560}, {\"ngram\": \"areas\", \"from\": 4569, \"to\": 4574}, {\"ngram\": \"the population\", \"from\": 4581, \"to\": 4595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At least 43 of the permits went to opponents of the hunt who never intend to use them, according to the Florida chapter of the Sierra Club, which encouraged critics to apply in the hopes of saving bears.\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4724, \"end\": 4731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 4747, \"end\": 4758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.60825024829776e-25, \"text\": \"Sierra Club\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sierra_Club\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the permits\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4646}, {\"ngram\": \"opponents\", \"from\": 4655, \"to\": 4664}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 4668, \"to\": 4676}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 4777, \"to\": 4784}, {\"ngram\": \"the hopes\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4806}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 4817, \"to\": 4822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Florida black bear population is considered one of the state's conservation success stories, having grown from just several hundred bears in the 1970s to an estimated more than 4,000 today.\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 5018, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Florida black bear population\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 4858}, {\"ngram\": \"the state's conservation success stories\", \"from\": 4880, \"to\": 4920}, {\"ngram\": \"just several hundred bears\", \"from\": 4940, \"to\": 4966}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1970s\", \"from\": 4970, \"to\": 4979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opponents have questioned whether the hunt was necessary, but they were unable to convince the courts to halt it.\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opponents\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5029}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 5054, \"to\": 5062}, {\"ngram\": \"the courts\", \"from\": 5111, \"to\": 5121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what to know.\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5155, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A limit of one bear per hunter The 172 people who were awarded a permit through a random lottery will be able to kill one bear each during the 2025 season, which runs from Dec. 6 to Dec. 28.\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5347, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A limit\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5164}, {\"ngram\": \"one bear\", \"from\": 5168, \"to\": 5176}, {\"ngram\": \"hunter\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5187}, {\"ngram\": \"The 172 people\", \"from\": 5188, \"to\": 5202}, {\"ngram\": \"a permit\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5228}, {\"ngram\": \"a random lottery\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5253}, {\"ngram\": \"one bear\", \"from\": 5275, \"to\": 5283}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2025 season\", \"from\": 5296, \"to\": 5311}, {\"ngram\": \"Dec.\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5333}, {\"ngram\": \"Dec.\", \"from\": 5339, \"to\": 5343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The permits are specific to one of the state's four designated bear hunting zones, each of which have a hunting quota set by state officials based on the bear population in each region.\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5533, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The permits\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5359}, {\"ngram\": \"the state's four designated bear hunting zones\", \"from\": 5383, \"to\": 5429}, {\"ngram\": \"a hunting quota\", \"from\": 5450, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"state officials\", \"from\": 5473, \"to\": 5488}, {\"ngram\": \"the bear population\", \"from\": 5498, \"to\": 5517}, {\"ngram\": \"each region\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In order to participate, hunters must hold a valid hunting license and a bear harvest permit, which costs $100 for residents and $300 for nonresidents, plus fees.\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 5538, \"to\": 5543}, {\"ngram\": \"hunters\", \"from\": 5560, \"to\": 5567}, {\"ngram\": \"a valid hunting license\", \"from\": 5578, \"to\": 5601}, {\"ngram\": \"a bear harvest permit\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5627}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 5650, \"to\": 5659}, {\"ngram\": \"nonresidents\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5685}, {\"ngram\": \"fees\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Applications for the permits cost $5 each.\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Applications\", \"from\": 5698, \"to\": 5710}, {\"ngram\": \"the permits\", \"from\": 5715, \"to\": 5726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The regulated hunt will help incentivize maintaining healthy bear populations, and help fund the work that is needed, according to Mark Barton of the Florida chapter of Backcountry Hunters and Anglers, an advocacy group that supported the hunt.\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5873, \"end\": 5884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\", \"score\": 0.9999996500637892, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mark Barton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_O._Barton\"}, {\"begin\": 5892, \"end\": 5899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The regulated hunt\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5760}, {\"ngram\": \"healthy bear populations\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5819}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 5835, \"to\": 5843}, {\"ngram\": \"Backcountry Hunters\", \"from\": 5911, \"to\": 5930}, {\"ngram\": \"Anglers\", \"from\": 5935, \"to\": 5942}, {\"ngram\": \"an advocacy group\", \"from\": 5944, \"to\": 5961}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 5977, \"to\": 5985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having an annual hunt will help guarantee funding to \\\"keep moving conservation for bears forward,\\\" Barton said.\", \"from\": 5988, \"to\": 6099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6087, \"end\": 6093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\", \"score\": 0.9964082497657656, \"rank\": 0.003604697406801381, \"text\": \"Barton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demesne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an annual hunt\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6009}, {\"ngram\": \"funding\", \"from\": 6030, \"to\": 6037}, {\"ngram\": \"conservation\", \"from\": 6054, \"to\": 6066}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 6071, \"to\": 6076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hunting as a management tool According to state wildlife officials, the bear population has grown enough to support a regulated hunt and warrant population management.\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6268, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a management tool\", \"from\": 6112, \"to\": 6129}, {\"ngram\": \"state wildlife officials\", \"from\": 6143, \"to\": 6167}, {\"ngram\": \"the bear population\", \"from\": 6169, \"to\": 6188}, {\"ngram\": \"a regulated hunt\", \"from\": 6217, \"to\": 6233}, {\"ngram\": \"warrant population management\", \"from\": 6238, \"to\": 6267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The state agency sees hunting as an effective tool that is used to manage wildlife populations around the world, and allows the state to monetize conservation efforts through permit and application fees.\", \"from\": 6269, \"to\": 6472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The state agency\", \"from\": 6269, \"to\": 6285}, {\"ngram\": \"an effective tool\", \"from\": 6302, \"to\": 6319}, {\"ngram\": \"wildlife populations\", \"from\": 6343, \"to\": 6363}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 6371, \"to\": 6380}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 6393, \"to\": 6402}, {\"ngram\": \"conservation efforts\", \"from\": 6415, \"to\": 6435}, {\"ngram\": \"permit\", \"from\": 6444, \"to\": 6450}, {\"ngram\": \"application fees\", \"from\": 6455, \"to\": 6471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"While we have enough suitable bear habitat to support our current bear population levels, if the four largest subpopulations continue to grow at current rates, we will not have enough habitat at some point in the future,\\\" reads a bear hunting guide published by the state wildlife commission.\", \"from\": 6474, \"to\": 6767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6747, \"end\": 6755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\", \"score\": 0.999999999742613, \"rank\": 2.571201635022594e-10, \"text\": \"wildlife\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wildlife\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enough suitable bear habitat\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6517}, {\"ngram\": \"our current bear population levels\", \"from\": 6529, \"to\": 6563}, {\"ngram\": \"the four largest subpopulations\", \"from\": 6568, \"to\": 6599}, {\"ngram\": \"current rates\", \"from\": 6620, \"to\": 6633}, {\"ngram\": \"enough habitat\", \"from\": 6652, \"to\": 6666}, {\"ngram\": \"some point\", \"from\": 6670, \"to\": 6680}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6694}, {\"ngram\": \"a bear hunting guide\", \"from\": 6703, \"to\": 6723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opponents meanwhile have called the hunt cruel, unnecessary and an excuse for hunters to bag a trophy animal when the real issue is the ever-growing human population encroaching on bear habitat.\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6963, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opponents\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6778}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt cruel, unnecessary and an excuse\", \"from\": 6801, \"to\": 6842}, {\"ngram\": \"hunters\", \"from\": 6847, \"to\": 6854}, {\"ngram\": \"a trophy animal\", \"from\": 6862, \"to\": 6877}, {\"ngram\": \"the real issue\", \"from\": 6883, \"to\": 6897}, {\"ngram\": \"the ever-growing human population\", \"from\": 6901, \"to\": 6934}, {\"ngram\": \"bear habitat\", \"from\": 6950, \"to\": 6962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stricter regulations than the last hunt This year's hunting plan has more stringent rules than the 2015 hunt, in which permits were provided to anyone who could pay for them, resulting in more than 3,700 permits issued.\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 7184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Stricter regulations\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 6985}, {\"ngram\": \"the last hunt\", \"from\": 6991, \"to\": 7004}, {\"ngram\": \"This year's hunting plan\", \"from\": 7005, \"to\": 7029}, {\"ngram\": \"more stringent rules\", \"from\": 7034, \"to\": 7054}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2015 hunt\", \"from\": 7060, \"to\": 7073}, {\"ngram\": \"permits\", \"from\": 7084, \"to\": 7091}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 7109, \"to\": 7115}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 3,700 permits\", \"from\": 7153, \"to\": 7176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That led to a chaotic event that was shut down days early.\", \"from\": 7185, \"to\": 7243, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a chaotic event\", \"from\": 7197, \"to\": 7212}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 7232, \"to\": 7236}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of the 304 bears killed, at least 38 were females with cubs, meaning the young bears may have died too.\", \"from\": 7244, \"to\": 7347, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 304 bears\", \"from\": 7247, \"to\": 7260}, {\"ngram\": \"females\", \"from\": 7286, \"to\": 7293}, {\"ngram\": \"cubs\", \"from\": 7299, \"to\": 7303}, {\"ngram\": \"the young bears\", \"from\": 7313, \"to\": 7328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, wildlife officials decided to call off the hunt after its second day after a higher than expected number of bears were killed, though hunters did not exceed the statewide quota.\", \"from\": 7349, \"to\": 7538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wildlife officials\", \"from\": 7361, \"to\": 7379}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 7400, \"to\": 7408}, {\"ngram\": \"its second day\", \"from\": 7415, \"to\": 7429}, {\"ngram\": \"a higher than expected number\", \"from\": 7436, \"to\": 7465}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 7469, \"to\": 7474}, {\"ngram\": \"hunters\", \"from\": 7495, \"to\": 7502}, {\"ngram\": \"the statewide quota\", \"from\": 7518, \"to\": 7537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Doug Moore regularly sees bears on the more than 6,000 acres of timberland that he manages in northeast Florida.\", \"from\": 7540, \"to\": 7652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7545, \"end\": 7550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.5822766930591649, \"rank\": 0.7173965778136162, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 7644, \"end\": 7651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.207929941487292e-21, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 7566, \"to\": 7571}, {\"ngram\": \"the more than 6,000 acres\", \"from\": 7575, \"to\": 7600}, {\"ngram\": \"timberland\", \"from\": 7604, \"to\": 7614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The president of a local hunting club, Moore is generally supportive of the new regulations for the bear hunt, even though he and his family members were not issued a permit this year.\", \"from\": 7653, \"to\": 7837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7692, \"end\": 7697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"score\": 0.5822766930591649, \"rank\": 0.7173965778136162, \"text\": \"Moore\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henry_Moore\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a local hunting club\", \"from\": 7670, \"to\": 7690}, {\"ngram\": \"the new regulations\", \"from\": 7725, \"to\": 7744}, {\"ngram\": \"the bear hunt\", \"from\": 7749, \"to\": 7762}, {\"ngram\": \"his family members\", \"from\": 7783, \"to\": 7801}, {\"ngram\": \"a permit\", \"from\": 7818, \"to\": 7826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moore described the management of the 2015 hunt as \\\"fouled up\\\" and \\\"totally wrong\\\" but said, \\\"they are doing it right this time.\\\"\", \"from\": 7839, \"to\": 7968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Moore\", \"from\": 7839, \"to\": 7844}, {\"ngram\": \"the management\", \"from\": 7855, \"to\": 7869}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2015 hunt\", \"from\": 7873, \"to\": 7886}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Activists were issued dozens of permits Backers of the hunt have said that growing numbers of bears present a safety problem, with local officials sharing reports of bears on porches, rooting through garbage cans and roaming neighborhoods and playgrounds.\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 8225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Activists\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 7979}, {\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 7992, \"to\": 7998}, {\"ngram\": \"permits\", \"from\": 8002, \"to\": 8009}, {\"ngram\": \"Backers\", \"from\": 8010, \"to\": 8017}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 8021, \"to\": 8029}, {\"ngram\": \"growing numbers\", \"from\": 8045, \"to\": 8060}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 8064, \"to\": 8069}, {\"ngram\": \"a safety problem\", \"from\": 8078, \"to\": 8094}, {\"ngram\": \"local officials\", \"from\": 8101, \"to\": 8116}, {\"ngram\": \"reports\", \"from\": 8125, \"to\": 8132}, {\"ngram\": \"bears\", \"from\": 8136, \"to\": 8141}, {\"ngram\": \"porches\", \"from\": 8145, \"to\": 8152}, {\"ngram\": \"garbage cans\", \"from\": 8170, \"to\": 8182}, {\"ngram\": \"neighborhoods\", \"from\": 8195, \"to\": 8208}, {\"ngram\": \"playgrounds\", \"from\": 8213, \"to\": 8224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Activists have argued that the state should instead focus on other means of curbing nuisance bears and assuring safety through better trash management.\", \"from\": 8227, \"to\": 8378, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Activists\", \"from\": 8227, \"to\": 8236}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 8254, \"to\": 8263}, {\"ngram\": \"other means\", \"from\": 8288, \"to\": 8299}, {\"ngram\": \"nuisance bears\", \"from\": 8311, \"to\": 8325}, {\"ngram\": \"safety\", \"from\": 8339, \"to\": 8345}, {\"ngram\": \"better trash management\", \"from\": 8354, \"to\": 8377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While opponents failed to convince a judge to stop the hunt, they were issued about a quarter of the overall permits, after activists applied for hunting tags they never intend to use.\", \"from\": 8380, \"to\": 8564, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opponents\", \"from\": 8386, \"to\": 8395}, {\"ngram\": \"a judge\", \"from\": 8415, \"to\": 8422}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 8431, \"to\": 8439}, {\"ngram\": \"about a quarter\", \"from\": 8458, \"to\": 8473}, {\"ngram\": \"the overall permits\", \"from\": 8477, \"to\": 8496}, {\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 8504, \"to\": 8513}, {\"ngram\": \"tags\", \"from\": 8534, \"to\": 8538}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Somewhere out there a bear will be walking the grounds of the Panhandle, and I gave them a stay of execution,\\\" said Joel Cleveland, an opponent of the hunt who was issued one of the permits.\", \"from\": 8566, \"to\": 8757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8688, \"end\": 8697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"score\": 0.8731683470142257, \"rank\": 0.14525452442177036, \"text\": \"Cleveland\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cleveland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bear\", \"from\": 8587, \"to\": 8593}, {\"ngram\": \"the grounds\", \"from\": 8610, \"to\": 8621}, {\"ngram\": \"the Panhandle\", \"from\": 8625, \"to\": 8638}, {\"ngram\": \"a stay\", \"from\": 8656, \"to\": 8662}, {\"ngram\": \"execution\", \"from\": 8666, \"to\": 8675}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent\", \"from\": 8699, \"to\": 8710}, {\"ngram\": \"the hunt\", \"from\": 8714, \"to\": 8722}, {\"ngram\": \"the permits\", \"from\": 8745, \"to\": 8756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A micro artist said he has beaten his own world record by creating the smallest handmade sculpture ever.\", \"from\": 8759, \"to\": 8863, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A micro artist\", \"from\": 8759, \"to\": 8773}, {\"ngram\": \"his own world record\", \"from\": 8793, \"to\": 8813}, {\"ngram\": \"the smallest handmade sculpture\", \"from\": 8826, \"to\": 8857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David A Lindon, from Bournemouth, Dorset, says his latest sculpture, The Yellow Smiley Face, is \\\"invisible to the human eye,\\\" with measurements of only 11.037 by 12.330 microns, according to BBC.\", \"from\": 8865, \"to\": 9060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8873, \"end\": 8879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}, {\"begin\": 8886, \"end\": 8897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\", \"score\": 0.9999999996443876, \"rank\": 3.558296567529667e-10, \"text\": \"Bournemouth\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bournemouth\"}, {\"begin\": 8899, \"end\": 8905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.041801248277773e-15, \"text\": \"Dorset\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dorset\"}, {\"begin\": 8945, \"end\": 8956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.33803129408417e-49, \"text\": \"Smiley Face\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Smiley\"}, {\"begin\": 9056, \"end\": 9059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9984114833355686, \"rank\": 0.0015910438296974658, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his latest sculpture\", \"from\": 8912, \"to\": 8932}, {\"ngram\": \"the human eye\", \"from\": 8975, \"to\": 8988}, {\"ngram\": \"measurements\", \"from\": 8996, \"to\": 9008}, {\"ngram\": \"12.330 microns\", \"from\": 9027, \"to\": 9041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindon said his artwork lived on a first-class stamp on a micro dot on the eye of the late Queen.\", \"from\": 9062, \"to\": 9159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9062, \"end\": 9068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his artwork\", \"from\": 9074, \"to\": 9085}, {\"ngram\": \"a first-class stamp\", \"from\": 9095, \"to\": 9114}, {\"ngram\": \"a micro dot\", \"from\": 9118, \"to\": 9129}, {\"ngram\": \"the eye\", \"from\": 9133, \"to\": 9140}, {\"ngram\": \"the late Queen\", \"from\": 9144, \"to\": 9158}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has now broken his previous smallest handmade sculpture world record, The Lego Brick.\", \"from\": 9161, \"to\": 9249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9238, \"end\": 9242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.162565819866807e-13, \"text\": \"Lego\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lego\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his previous smallest handmade sculpture world record\", \"from\": 9179, \"to\": 9232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lindon, who has 12 Guinness World Records in total, is known for his work creating miniature pieces of art, including three microscopic re-creations of Van Gogh masterpieces on a watch mechanism which sold for \\u00a390,000.\", \"from\": 9251, \"to\": 9469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9251, \"end\": 9257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4672976126423855e-37, \"text\": \"Lindon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geography_of_Middle-earth\"}, {\"begin\": 9270, \"end\": 9292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.029739423524005e-53, \"text\": \"Guinness World Records\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guinness_World_Records\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 9296, \"to\": 9301}, {\"ngram\": \"his work\", \"from\": 9316, \"to\": 9324}, {\"ngram\": \"miniature pieces\", \"from\": 9334, \"to\": 9350}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 9354, \"to\": 9357}, {\"ngram\": \"three microscopic re\", \"from\": 9369, \"to\": 9389}, {\"ngram\": \"creations\", \"from\": 9390, \"to\": 9399}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh masterpieces\", \"from\": 9403, \"to\": 9424}, {\"ngram\": \"a watch mechanism\", \"from\": 9428, \"to\": 9445}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Red Lego Brick measures 0.02517mm by 0.02184mm.\", \"from\": 9471, \"to\": 9522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Red Lego Brick\", \"from\": 9471, \"to\": 9489}, {\"ngram\": \"0.02184mm\", \"from\": 9512, \"to\": 9521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My Yellow Smiley Face artwork is half the size of my Red Lego Brick artwork, which in turn was already four times smaller than the previous record,\\\" the artist said.\", \"from\": 9524, \"to\": 9690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My Yellow Smiley Face artwork\", \"from\": 9525, \"to\": 9554}, {\"ngram\": \"half the size\", \"from\": 9558, \"to\": 9571}, {\"ngram\": \"my Red Lego Brick artwork\", \"from\": 9575, \"to\": 9600}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 9611, \"to\": 9615}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous record\", \"from\": 9652, \"to\": 9671}, {\"ngram\": \"the artist\", \"from\": 9674, \"to\": 9684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said it was the same size as either a human blood cell, mould spores, bacteria, talcum powder and a fog droplet.\", \"from\": 9692, \"to\": 9807, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same size\", \"from\": 9707, \"to\": 9720}, {\"ngram\": \"either a human blood cell\", \"from\": 9724, \"to\": 9749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other of Lindon's tiny creations include unique animals crafted within the eye of a needle, from a blue whale to a delicate peacock butterfly.\", \"from\": 9809, \"to\": 9951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9818, \"end\": 9824, \